The service isn't. Wait staff very casual. Literally just having a chat with the tender while we wait for them to take our order (waited 15 minutes to place an order when it wasn't even busy).

Folks behind the sushi bar crushing beers left and right. I'm not against drinking, but this is highly unprofessional. The guys literally crouched down to consume their apparently "hidden" on-the-job drinking (you're working directly in front of me). Also handling some food with bare hands. Not a good scene even with many community members vaccinated.

The sushi rolls are very good. Very pricey, but I'd say in terms of taste, presentation, and amount, you get what you pay for (perhaps a bit pricey). In terms of service, absolutely not. If the service was even halfway decent, I'd give this at least 4 stars.', 'time': 1623905617}]

We had nachos with potato chips and they were really good. It was a nice twist on original nachos—they give you options, too which I really liked. We also ordered the fish and chips, cottage pie and a pick-your-protein kinda of deal with blackened cod. The music was a bit loud, but I just got off work and wanted to unwind, SO... give me a margarita and turn it up!! I loved it!! Go to Thomas Meagher and ask for Hannah. She'll take perfect care of you. Thank you and we'll be back soon.", 'time': 1618097177}]

Hours_Open: ['Monday: Closed', 'Tuesday: Closed', 'Wednesday: Closed', 'Thursday: Closed', 'Friday: 8:00 AM – 2:00 PM', 'Saturday: 8:00 AM – 2:00 PM', 'Sunday: 8:00 AM – 2:00 PM']
reviews: [{'author_name': 'Megan Zmak', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101809510862429964760/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GheN-inmfVV9xx6jZv2z3LpJhNibFaFFvYD5oHw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '4 months ago', 'text': 'Walked in at 11am on a Saturday morning. Was told it would be a 25-30min wait. We waited 30min and they seated the 4 of us. The first staff member brought us water right away. A few minutes later our waitress came by and introduced herself and asked if we wanted anything else to drink besides water. The entire front page of the menu is all alcoholic beverages. When I asked to order a mimosa, the waitress informed me that they sold their liquor license 2 months ago. I’m curious as to why the entire front page of the menu still advertises alcohol if they no longer sell any? There were no signs in or outside the restaurant that informed me as a customer of this change. The waitress left our table and said she would be back shortly to take our orders. She came back promptly and we ordered our food. We sat and waited for an hour and 12 minutes. Our waitress had come by once in that time and said “oh you haven’t gotten your food yet?” Why didn’t my waitress know when my food was arriving at my table? Isn’t that their entire job? I asked another employee walking by if she could check on our food. A little while had passed and our original waitress came back and said “Sorry, your order ticket got lost. Do you want me to ring it in for you now?” I said no I’m not waiting any longer and I left. Very very disappointed in the service. At least 5 other employees passed near our table within that hour and didn’t think to check on us. Probably won’t be going back.', 'time': 1625944378}, {'author_name': 'Sarah Jacklin', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113092957174202266881/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJyO2t2S990B5MDQe-mYkAsgNIbgXM6sIJv7il1t=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': 'Went in for breakfast for two, was told it would be a 30 min wait when there were plenty of open tables for two as well as larger booths. We ventured around until they called us to inform us they were ready to seat us! Waters quickly brought to the table and server arrived moments later to get our order… prices could use some modifying on some drink orders for sure… regular diner coffee cost me more than my espresso drinks at coffee kiosks!!! All food was lacking flavor and drinks sat empty without refill after server walked by 9 times… bus boy came by once and filled our drinks so there is a positive point there! Corned beef and hash lacking corned beef, chicken fried steak just tasted like deep fried flour… so disappointing as I read reviews and menu pictures looked great!! They should DEFINITELY go back to the original way of making their sautéed veggies with the nice layer of crispy spuds topped with a layer of sautéed veggies covered in cheese. I think I may stop ordering my fav thing on their menu if they don’t. The corned beef hash was merely their usual hash browns with chopped up pieces of sausage in it, not corned beef, or at least it was unrecognizable as such. Everyone at my table ordered fresh squeezed orange juice and coffee, I ordered a latte and it didn’t arrive until a good 5 plus minutes after everyone else was served and there was never an offer for a refill on the drip coffee we ordered the entire time we were there. Nashville wings as appetizers tasted great, reminded me of living in Nashville and getting chicken with friends. Wonderful rubbed spice and the blue cheese dipping sauce was great with or without. A cauliflower option would be amazing!

Bison burger only comes cooked medium here, and that's okay. It was really good. Didn't feel greasy or overbearing. I love venison and bison, so I appreciate it done well in a burger.

Pulled pork was also just, super good. I only stole a couple bites from my boyfriend's plate... but... I really enjoyed the pulled pork. I believe it had a Carolina tangy sweetness that wasn't entirely like some of the Carolina BBQs I loved when I lived in NC, but still very good. I'd definitely come order it myself another time to fully experience.
